#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Sekkhasutta → sekho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Sekkhasutta"
msgstr "13. A Trainee"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.13:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn45.13:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn45.13:1.3"
msgid "“‘sekkho, sekkho’ti, bhante, vuccati."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this person called ‘a trainee’."

msgctxt "sn45.13:1.4"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sekkho hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How is a trainee defined?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.13:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhu, sekkhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti … pe … sekkhena "
"sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, it’s someone who has a trainee’s right view, right thought, "
"right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right "
"mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "sn45.13:2.2"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhu, sekkho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how a trainee is defined.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.13:2.3"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
